    "description": "Nix, Inc. plans, develops, manufactures, and sells industrial plastics parts, plastic fasteners, and other components in Japan and internationally. It provides label printing, NPID, pre-reflow labels, post-reflow labels, label printers, and label creation software; substrate cleaner; and PCB racks. The company also engages in planning, development, manufacturing, and sales of plastic mechanical parts, magazine racks, related peripheral equipment, labels, label applicators, and other label-related products, as well as parts using plastic materials. It serves office and production equipment, automobiles, housing equipment, and environmental sanitation industries through trading companies and sales agents. The company was formerly known as Nikko Kogyo Corporation and changed its name to Nix, Inc. in 2001. Nix, Inc. was incorporated in 1949 and is headquartered in Yokohama, Japan."
